title.narrative: VN-Red River Delta Rural Water Supply and Sanitation Project

description.narrative: The development objective is to improve water and household level sanitation services and their effective use in selected provinces in ways that are financially, technically, and environmentally sustainable, thereby contributing to poverty alleviation in participating rural communities.

condition.narrative: Implementation partners that manage the Household Water and Sanitation Revolving Funds to maintain financial records and accountsfor the funds and have them audited annually.
Participating provinces and RWSSEs to establish water supply tariffs that cover operations, maintenance and debt repayment costsfor new piped water supply schemes.
Participating provinces to establish one or more Rural Water Supply Enterprises to be responsible for the construction, operation&management of piped water supply schemes.
RWSSEs to establish water supply tariffs that cover operations, maintenance and depreciation costs for existing piped water supplyschemes transferred to them.
